comment_data.body:
@gpanders, I don't think the check can make that distinction: https://clang.llvm.org/extra/clang-tidy/checks/readability-isolate-declaration.html

It's quite useful for pointers, so I guess it depends how often do you think it could happen. 

One possibility is to fix the initializer but keep the others, and eventually turn off the check and leave it for the reviewers to enforce the rule.

